this is a typical ceremony of a Muslim wedding - “Maanja” as we call it, which has also evolved into the Sangeet event leading upto the main wedding day. 
This ceremony has a very unique fashion quotient prevalent in the family and culture I come from - you see how most girls are wearing silver embellished outfits? The work on the outfit is called Chaapa - It’s a traditional bridal outfit with silver block print. This dress was especially designed to be worn by the bride on the day of Nikah and the history of this traditional dress can be traced back to the nineteenth century.

These are lines from a poem “The Invitation” by Oriah. 

As daughters ( and sons too in a lot of cases ) we are raised to never disappoint, our parents, teaches, society. To bow your head, do as they say. Don’t question, don’t argue. Just follow the path someone else has created for you. 

Until you realise, you are being unfaithful to yourself, until one fine day your heart gives up on things the head commands it to do. 

Re-writing the paragraph from the poem for you to read again-

“I want to know if you can
disappoint another
to be true to yourself.
If you can bear
the accusation of betrayal
and not betray your own soul.
If you can be faithless
and therefore trustworthy.”

Does this resonate with you?

I started my journey in India, and eventually ventured to the US for school. After spending three years in the oil and gas industry, the pandemic hit and oil prices plummeted, causing me to lose my job. But I refused to let this setback bring me down. I decided to pursue a Ph.D. program in Business. 
Despite the unexpected change in my plans, I drew on my experience as a content creator to make meaningful connections in the South Asian community. This led me to create “Recover Season,” as a reminder for self-reflection on personal growth, accomplishments, and mental health. I chose the colors of the sunset - purple, pink, yellow, and orange - to symbolize the tranquility and fortitude we should always carry with us.
In crafting my collection, I prioritize using Indian fabrics, glass work, laces, and tassels, with everything being handmade and hand-stitched. Sustainability is at the forefront of my mind, we use viscose, cotton or deadstock fabrics. 
Additionally, through @recoverseason , I’ve been able to learn more about my family’s entrepreneurial spirit. As my mom and dad retired from demanding jobs, they jumped on to help lead RS. Family holds a special place in my heart and through this experience, I’ve become closer with my parents and gained a deeper understanding of the parent-child relationship.
What sets my collection apart is not only its focus on sustainability and unique colors but also the family aspect that underpins it all. Our family values togetherness and through Recover Season, we have been able to come together and support each other, one step at a time.

Could be my very first attempt to be a designer or an interior decorator or an hairstylist. 🥲

With over 50 Barbies and her relatives, it’s  are still one of my most priced possessions.
Thanks to the @barbiethemovie , those Vintage Barbies are now of great value.

few of my fav moments from NYC ✨🗽

Mercury Retrograde got me feeling bit anxious lately and had this thought . Don’t you think looking nice and feeling bright and glowy all the time is putting just too much pressure on yourself!? 

It’s natural to feel anxious or overwhelmed, especially in a society that often equates appearance with worth or success. The constant emphasis on looking “nice” or appearing “bright and glowy” can indeed lead to an immense amount of pressure. This expectation to always be at one’s best – not just physically, but also mentally and emotionally – is not only unrealistic but can also be detrimental.

This is a reminder to remember that everyone has off days, and nobody is perfect all the time. Emotions, including anxiety, are a natural part of the human experience. They serve as indicators of our internal state and can be signals that we need to pause, reflect, or seek support.

It’s essential to prioritize mental and emotional well-being over superficial expectations.

did you know 

The 11:00 pm magic around Eiffel Tower when it glitters for five mins? 
The magic never gets old, but electricity for 20,000 lightbulbs is crazy! 
The Eiffel Tower lights up after dark and used to sparkle every hour for 5 minutes until 1:00 am. In 2022, as part of a cost-saving measure, the authorities decided that the iconic sparkles would occur only once per night, at 11:00 pm for 5 minutes exactly. And the Iron Lady goes completely dark at 11:45 pm. #parisfrance #eiffeltoweratnight #thingstodoinparis #parisbucketlist

📍 Milano 

Milan is a city in northern Italy that is known for its rich history, stunning architecture, and vibrant culture.
The city is home to some of the most iconic landmarks in Italy, including the Duomo di Milano, a Gothic cathedral that took nearly 600 years to complete and is one of the largest churches in the world.

Explore the intricate architecture of the Duomo di
Milano, appreciate the hub of fashion business and indulge in fashion and shopping in the Galleria Vittorio Emanuel II. Don’t miss the dinner at Osteria de fortuna 🍝.

Save this post for your next visit to Milan

🥂 I am spending the holidays alone, probably the first time ever. I absolutely love it. Haha. Growing up the only child, I dont get lonely easy. 

In my opinion, it’s crucial to spend time with yourself, and such weekends help to check in with yourself and your loved ones. Its a great opportunity to create vision boards, five year goals, work on business plans and journaling. 

If you are spending the holidays alone, or feeling alone, do try and check in with yourself. Take yourself out and indulge in something you love. 👸🏻 🥂🎀

had heard that if you want to experience the true beauty of Hawa Mahal, see it at night. It indeed is beyond mesmerizing!

Hawa Mahal Jaipur, popularly known as the ‘Palace of Winds,’ is a renowned tourist destination and prominent monument in the pink city. 

Built for females in royal palace, it was from these windows that the royal women would observe street processions and daily life without being seen. 

What I also admire about Hawa Mahal is, it also is a cultural and architectural marvel that reflects a truly harmonious amalgamation of the Hindu Rajput and Islamic Mughal architectural styles. Harmony and diversity brings out such beauty ✨🎀💜. #pinkcityjaipur
